From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000053 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Julien Etienne <julien.etienne@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 00:00:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: mediatek: gemini: add TOPRGU watchdog IRQ

The Gemini vendor DT describes the MT6797 TOPRGU at 0x10007000 with
GIC SPI137, falling-edge triggered. Linux 7.1.3 already reuses the
generic MediaTek watchdog driver for the mt6797-wdt/mt6589-wdt pair, but
the shared SoC node does not carry the board's bark interrupt. Add the
interrupt on the Gemini board so the standard watchdog interface can
report a pretimeout without changing reset-output policy.

The watchdog remains owned by the normal Linux watchdog core; no vendor
WDK character ABI or reset-request side channel is introduced.

Signed-off-by: Julien Etienne <julien.etienne@gmail.com>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt6797-gemini-pda.dts | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt6797-gemini-pda.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt6797-gemini-pda.dts
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt6797-gemini-pda.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt6797-gemini-pda.dts
@@ -235,3 +235,7 @@
 		status = "disabled";
 	};
 };
+
+&watchdog {
+	interrupts = <GIC_SPI 137 IRQ_TYPE_EDGE_FALLING>;
+};
-- 
